ualstudio#administrator-update-command-and-command-line-parameters" aria-la=
bel=3D"Section titled: Administrator Update command and command-line parame=
ters"></a><h2 id=3D"administrator-update-command-and-command-line-parameter=
s" class=3D"heading-anchor">Administrator Update command and command-line p=
arameters</h2></div>
<p>You can download an <strong>Administrator Update</strong> from the <a hr=
ef=3D"https://catalog.update.microsoft.com/" data-linktype=3D"external">Mic=
rosoft Update Catalog</a> and use it to update either your client installat=
ion or your layout.</p>
<div class=3D"heading-wrapper" data-heading-level=3D"h3"><a class=3D"anchor=
-link docon docon-link" href=3D"https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/visualstu=
dio/install/use-command-line-parameters-to-install-visual-studio?view=3Dvis=
ualstudio#updating-a-layout" aria-label=3D"Section titled: Updating a layou=
t"></a><h3 id=3D"updating-a-layout" class=3D"heading-anchor">Updating a lay=
out</h3></div>
<p>If you're updating a layout to a particular version of Visual Studio, ju=
st download the Administrator Update to the computer that's hosting the lay=
out, open up a command prompt on that computer and run a command like this:=
</p>
<div class=3D"code-block-header margin-top-sm" data-code-block-header=3D"" =
id=3D"code-try-6" data-bi-name=3D"code-header"><!---->
		<span class=3D"code-block-header-language">
			shell
		</span>
		<div class=3D"code-block-header-action-bar"><!---->
		<button type=3D"button" class=3D"button display-none-print" data-bi-name=
=3D"copy" data-code-header-copy-button=3D"">
			<span class=3D"icon" aria-hidden=3D"true">
				<span class=3D"docon docon-edit-copy overflow-hidden"></span>
				<span data-copy-button-success-indicator=3D"" class=3D"successful-copy-=
alert position-absolute is-transparent docon docon-check-mark"></span>
			</span>
			<span><!---->Copy<!----></span>
		</button>
	 <!----></div>
	<!----></div><pre class=3D"inner-focus" data-language=3D"shell"><code clas=
s=3D"lang-shell"><span>visualstudioupdate-17.0.0to17.1.5.exe layout --layou=
tPath c:\VSLayout
</span></code></pre>
<div class=3D"heading-wrapper" data-heading-level=3D"h3"><a class=3D"anchor=
-link docon docon-link" href=3D"https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/visualstu=
dio/install/use-command-line-parameters-to-install-visual-studio?view=3Dvis=
ualstudio#updating-a-client" aria-label=3D"Section titled: Updating a clien=
t"></a><h3 id=3D"updating-a-client" class=3D"heading-anchor">Updating a cli=
ent</h3></div>
<p>On the client, if you download the Administrator Update into your instal=
lation directory on your client machine, you can just double-click on the f=
ile to apply the update. You can also open a command window and pass some o=
f the parameters below to change the default behavior.</p>
<div class=3D"heading-wrapper" data-heading-level=3D"h3"><a class=3D"anchor=
-link docon docon-link" href=3D"https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/visualstu=
dio/install/use-command-line-parameters-to-install-visual-studio?view=3Dvis=
ualstudio#configuring-the-administrator-update-in-sccm" aria-label=3D"Secti=
on titled: Configuring the Administrator Update in SCCM"></a><h3 id=3D"conf=
iguring-the-administrator-update-in-sccm" class=3D"heading-anchor">Configur=
ing the Administrator Update in SCCM</h3></div>
<p>If you're deploying the administrator update through Microsoft Endpoint =
Manager (SCCM), you can modify the package to adjust the behavior by using =
the parameters below. You can also control the parameters via a configurati=
on file on the client machine. For more information, refer to <a href=3D"ht=
tps://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/visualstudio/install/applying-administrator=
-updates?view=3Dvisualstudio#methods-for-configuring-an-administrator-updat=
e" data-linktype=3D"relative-path">Methods for configuring an administrator=
 update</a></p>
<p>Note that all Administrator Update parameters are default run in the "up=
date" context unless the layout verb is specified.</p>
<div class=3D"buttons buttons-right margin-bottom-none margin-top-sm"><!---=
-> <button class=3D"button button-clear button-sm display-flex gap-xxs">
		<span class=3D"icon" aria-hidden=3D"true">
			<span class=3D"docon docon-expand color-primary"></span>
		</span>
		<span><!---->Expand table<!----></span>
	</button><!----></div><div class=3D"inner-focus"><table aria-label=3D"Conf=
iguring the Administrator Update in SCCM" class=3D"table table-sm margin-to=
p-none">
<thead>
<tr>
<th><strong>Administrator update parameters</strong></th>
<th><strong>Description</strong></th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><code>--installerUpdateArgs [optional parameters]</code></td>
<td>This parameter functions as a "pass-through array" of specific paramete=
rs that are relevant to administrator update scenarios. Optional parameters=
 that are enabled for this purpose are: <br><br> <code>--quiet</code>: This=
 is the default experience for administrator updates and is listed here for=
 completeness. <br> <code>--passive</code>: This parameter overrides the <c=
ode>--quiet</code> parameter.  It causes the UI to appear in a non-interact=
ive manner. <br><code>--norestart</code>: This parameter must be used in co=
njunction with either <code>--quiet</code> or <code>--passive</code> and it=
 causes any necessary reboots to be delayed. <br><code>--noWeb</code>: This=
 parameter prevents Visual Studio from checking on the internet for updates=
 to the product. <br><code>--force</code>: This parameter forces Visual Stu=
dio to close even if Visual Studio is in use. Use this parameter with cauti=
on, as it may cause loss of work. This parameter must only be used when the=
 Administrator update is executed in user context; it is ignored if the Adm=
inistrator update is executed in system context. <br><code>--installWhileDo=
wnloading</code>: This parameter allows Visual Studio to both download and =
install the product in parallel. It's the default experience for administra=
tor updates and is listed here for completeness. <br><code>--keepWindowsUpd=
ateOn</code>: This parameter prevents the installer from turning off the Wi=
ndows Update agent on the client. You should use this parameter if you're i=
mporting an Administrator update from the Catalog into SCCM. You may also n=
eed to set the SCCM package timeout to be longer than the default 10 minute=
s. Changing the SCCM deployment type to be Required makes this parameter un=
necessary.<br><code>--downloadThenInstall</code>: This parameter forces Vis=
ual Studio to download all files before installing them. It is mutually exc=
lusive from the <code>--installWhileDownloading</code> parameter.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>--checkPendingReboot</code></td>
<td>The update will be aborted if there is a pending reboot on the machine,=
 regardless of which application may have caused it. The default is to not =
check for pending reboots.</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table></div>
<p>Syntax example for passing parameters into an Administrator update:</p>
<div class=3D"code-block-header margin-top-sm" data-code-block-header=3D"" =
id=3D"code-try-7" data-bi-name=3D"code-header"><!---->
