alert position-absolute is-transparent docon docon-check-mark"></span>
			</span>
			<span><!---->Copy<!----></span>
		</button>
	 <!----></div>
	<!----></div><pre class=3D"inner-focus" role=3D"group" aria-label=3D"Horiz=
ontally scrollable code" tabindex=3D"0" data-language=3D"shell"><code class=
=3D"lang-shell"><span>visualstudioupdate-16.9.0to16.9.4.exe --installerUpda=
teArgs=3D--force,--noWeb,--keepWindowsUpdateOn --checkPendingReboot
</span></code></pre>
<div class=3D"heading-wrapper" data-heading-level=3D"h2"><a class=3D"anchor=
-link docon docon-link" href=3D"https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/visualstu=
dio/install/use-command-line-parameters-to-install-visual-studio?view=3Dvis=
ualstudio#remove-channel-command-and-command-line-parameters" aria-label=3D=
"Section titled: Remove channel command and command-line parameters"></a><h=
2 id=3D"remove-channel-command-and-command-line-parameters" class=3D"headin=
g-anchor">Remove channel command and command-line parameters</h2></div>
<p>Channels that are available to update from, are cached on the client, an=
d over time they can clutter things up. You can manually remove <a href=3D"=
https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/visualstudio/install/update-visual-studio=
?view=3Dvisualstudio#configure-source-location-of-updates-1" data-linktype=
=3D"relative-path">update channels</a> by bringing up the Visual Studio Ins=
taller, switching to the <strong>Available</strong> tab, and clicking on th=
e <strong>X</strong> in the top right corner of the product card. You can p=
rogrammatically remove channels (for example, older layout locations) using=
 the <code>removeChannel</code> command. You can run <a href=3D"https://lea=
rn.microsoft.com/en-us/visualstudio/install/tools-for-managing-visual-studi=
o-instances?view=3Dvisualstudio#using-vswhereexe" data-linktype=3D"relative=
-path">vswhere</a> programmatically on the client machine to determine whic=
h channels are cached on the client machine.</p>
<div class=3D"buttons buttons-right margin-bottom-none margin-top-sm"><!---=
-> <button class=3D"button button-clear button-sm display-flex gap-xxs">
		<span class=3D"icon" aria-hidden=3D"true">
			<span class=3D"docon docon-expand color-primary"></span>
		</span>
		<span><!---->Expand table<!----></span>
	</button><!----></div><div class=3D"inner-focus"><table aria-label=3D"Remo=
ve channel command and command-line parameters" class=3D"table table-sm mar=
gin-top-none">
<thead>
<tr>
<th><strong>Command</strong></th>
<th><strong>Description</strong></th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><code>removeChannel</code></td>
<td>Command to remove a channel from the client machine.</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table></div>
<div class=3D"buttons buttons-right margin-bottom-none margin-top-sm"><!---=
-> <button class=3D"button button-clear button-sm display-flex gap-xxs">
		<span class=3D"icon" aria-hidden=3D"true">
			<span class=3D"docon docon-expand color-primary"></span>
		</span>
		<span><!---->Expand table<!----></span>
	</button><!----></div><div class=3D"inner-focus"><table aria-label=3D"Remo=
ve channel command and command-line parameters" class=3D"table table-sm mar=
gin-top-none">
<thead>
<tr>
<th><strong>removeChannel parameters</strong></th>
<th><strong>Description</strong></th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><code>--channelUri</code></td>
<td><strong>Required</strong> The URI of the old channel manifest.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>--quiet</code></td>
<td><strong>Optional</strong> This parameter prevents any user interface fr=
om being displayed while the command is being executed.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>--passive</code></td>
<td><strong>Optional</strong> This parameter overrides the <code>--quiet</c=
ode> parameter.  It causes the UI to appear in a non-interactive manner.</t=
d>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table></div>
<p>Syntax example:</p>
<div class=3D"code-block-header margin-top-sm" data-code-block-header=3D"" =
id=3D"code-try-8" data-bi-name=3D"code-header"><!---->
		<span class=3D"code-block-header-language">
			shell
		</span>
