=3D"lang-shell"><span>"C:\Program Files (x86)\Microsoft Visual Studio\Insta=
ller\setup.exe" removeChannel --channelUri "\\\\server\\share\\layoutdirect=
ory\\ChannelManifest.json"
</span></code></pre>
<div class=3D"heading-wrapper" data-heading-level=3D"h2"><a class=3D"anchor=
-link docon docon-link" href=3D"https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/visualstu=
dio/install/use-command-line-parameters-to-install-visual-studio?view=3Dvis=
ualstudio#use-winget-to-install-or-modify-visual-studio" aria-label=3D"Sect=
ion titled: Use winget to install or modify Visual Studio"></a><h2 id=3D"us=
e-winget-to-install-or-modify-visual-studio" class=3D"heading-anchor">Use w=
inget to install or modify Visual Studio</h2></div>
<p>You can use the <a href=3D"https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/pac=
kage-manager/winget/" data-linktype=3D"absolute-path">Windows Package Manag=
er</a> "winget" tool to programmatically install, modify, or update Visual =
Studio on your machine along with other packages managed by winget.</p>
<div data-moniker=3D"visualstudio">
<p>By default, winget just installs the Visual Studio core workload.</p>
<div class=3D"code-block-header margin-top-sm" data-code-block-header=3D"" =
id=3D"code-try-9" data-bi-name=3D"code-header"><!---->
		<span class=3D"code-block-header-language">
			shell
		</span>
		<div class=3D"code-block-header-action-bar"><!---->
		<button type=3D"button" class=3D"button display-none-print" data-bi-name=
=3D"copy" data-code-header-copy-button=3D"">
			<span class=3D"icon" aria-hidden=3D"true">
				<span class=3D"docon docon-edit-copy overflow-hidden"></span>
				<span data-copy-button-success-indicator=3D"" class=3D"successful-copy-=
alert position-absolute is-transparent docon docon-check-mark"></span>
			</span>
			<span><!---->Copy<!----></span>
		</button>
	 <!----></div>
	<!----></div><pre class=3D"inner-focus" data-language=3D"shell"><code clas=
s=3D"lang-shell"><span>winget install --id Microsoft.VisualStudio.Community
</span></code></pre>
<p>However, if you want to customize the installation and specify additiona=
l workloads and components to acquire during initial installation, you can =
use winget's <code>--override</code> switch alongside winget's <code>instal=
l</code> command, and pass in an <a href=3D"https://learn.microsoft.com/en-=
us/visualstudio/install/import-export-installation-configurations?view=3Dvi=
sualstudio" data-linktype=3D"relative-path">exported vsconfig file</a> that=
 contains the workloads and components to add:</p>
<div class=3D"code-block-header margin-top-sm" data-code-block-header=3D"" =
id=3D"code-try-10" data-bi-name=3D"code-header"><!---->
		<span class=3D"code-block-header-language">
			shell
		</span>
		<div class=3D"code-block-header-action-bar"><!---->
		<button type=3D"button" class=3D"button display-none-print" data-bi-name=
=3D"copy" data-code-header-copy-button=3D"">
			<span class=3D"icon" aria-hidden=3D"true">
				<span class=3D"docon docon-edit-copy overflow-hidden"></span>
				<span data-copy-button-success-indicator=3D"" class=3D"successful-copy-=
alert position-absolute is-transparent docon docon-check-mark"></span>
			</span>
			<span><!---->Copy<!----></span>
		</button>
	 <!----></div>
	<!----></div><pre class=3D"inner-focus" data-language=3D"shell"><code clas=
s=3D"lang-shell"><span>winget install --id Microsoft.VisualStudio.Community=
 --override "--passive --config c:\my.vsconfig"
</span></code></pre>
<p>Of course, you can also just include components directly during the init=
ial installation, like this:</p>
<div class=3D"code-block-header margin-top-sm" data-code-block-header=3D"" =
id=3D"code-try-11" data-bi-name=3D"code-header"><!---->
