ualstudio#support-or-troubleshooting" aria-label=3D"Section titled: Support=
 or troubleshooting"></a><h2 id=3D"support-or-troubleshooting" class=3D"hea=
ding-anchor">Support or troubleshooting</h2></div>
<p>Sometimes, things can go wrong. If your Visual Studio installation fails=
, see <a href=3D"https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/visualstudio/install/tro=
ubleshooting-installation-issues?view=3Dvisualstudio" data-linktype=3D"rela=
tive-path">Troubleshoot Visual Studio installation and upgrade issues</a> f=
or step-by-step guidance.</p>
<p>Here are a few more support options:</p>
<ul>
<li>Use the <a href=3D"https://visualstudio.microsoft.com/vs/support/#talkt=
ous" data-linktype=3D"external">installation chat</a> (English only) suppor=
t option for installation-related issues.</li>
<li>Report product issues to us by using the <a href=3D"https://learn.micro=
soft.com/en-us/visualstudio/ide/how-to-report-a-problem-with-visual-studio?=
view=3Dvisualstudio" data-linktype=3D"relative-path">Report a Problem</a> t=
ool that appears both in the Visual Studio Installer and in the Visual Stud=
io IDE. If you're an IT Administrator and don't have Visual Studio installe=
d, you can submit <a href=3D"https://aka.ms/vs/admin/feedback" data-linktyp=
e=3D"external">IT Admin feedback</a>.</li>
<li>Suggest a feature, track product issues, and find answers in the <a hre=
f=3D"https://aka.ms/feedback/suggest?space=3D8" data-linktype=3D"external">=
Visual Studio Developer Community</a>.</li>
</ul>
